Package com.pandora.config.species.abstractions

package com.pandora.config.species.abstractions
The com.pandora.config.species.abstractions package contains abstractions for representing biogeochemical species in a freshwater context. These abstractions define common characteristics and behaviors shared among different types of species, including aqueous and sedimentary species.

The package includes the following classes and interfaces:

  • SpecieConfiguration: An interface providing methods to retrieve configuration parameters for a biogeochemical species.
  • SpecieLogic: An interface defining the logic for calculating the transport of a biogeochemical species based on given parameters such as amount and discharge.
  • Specie: An abstract class that serves as the base for biogeochemical species, implementing both SpecieConfiguration and SpecieLogic interfaces.
  • AqueousSpecie: An abstract class extending Specie and providing a specific implementation of the calculateTransport method for aqueous species.
  • SedimentarySpecie: An abstract class extending Specie and providing a specific implementation of the calculateTransport method for sedimentary species.

Developers extending or implementing these abstractions should refer to the documentation of individual classes and interfaces for detailed information on their purposes and methods.

    Description
    AqueousSpecie
    The AqueousSpecie abstract class extends the Specie class and provides a concrete implementation of the SpecieLogic interface by overriding the AqueousSpecie.calculateTransport(double, double) method.
    SedimentarySpecie
    The SedimentarySpecie abstract class extends the Specie class and provides a concrete implementation of the SpecieLogic interface by overriding the SedimentarySpecie.calculateTransport(double, double) method.
    Specie
    The Specie abstract class extends the Variable class and implements both the SpecieConfiguration and SpecieLogic interfaces.
    SpecieConfiguration
    The SpecieConfiguration interface extends the VariableConfiguration interface and provides an additional method for retrieving the molar mass of the biogeochemical species.
    SpecieLogic
    The SpecieLogic interface defines methods for calculating the transport of a biogeochemical species in the freshwater system.
